World Health Organization (WHO) of three times the national gross domestic 
product (GDP) per capita (BRL 72,195). Regarding life expectancy (15 years), the 
incremental benefit of IMRT was 1.16 QALYs gained per person, with an ICER of 
BRL 4,341. IMRT was also cost-effective using the WHO definition, which states 
that the maximum cost is equal to the GDP per capita (BRL 24,065).
CONCLUSIONS: IMRT was considered cost-effective from the perspective of the 
Brazilian public health system.

